hed</ref> Maj Samuel Moody '''(w)'''\n* [[109th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|109th New York]]: Col [[Benjamin F. Tracy]]\n* [[51st Pennsylvania Infantry|51st Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Edwin Schall\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Benjamin C. Christ]]\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Michigan Volunteer Sharpshooters|1st Michigan Sharpshooters]]: Col Charles V. De Land\n* [[20th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|20th Michigan]]: Ltc [[Byron M. Cutcheon]]\n* [[79th New York Volunteer Infantry|79th New York]]:<ref name=after>Detached at Warrenton Junction; rejoined Brigade on May 7, 1864 (''see: Cutcheon's report'')</ref> Col David Morrison\n* [[60th Ohio Infantry|60th Ohio]]:<ref name=after/><ref>9th and 10th Companies Ohio Sharpshooters attached</ref> Ltc James N. McElroy\n* [[50th Pennsylvania Infantry|50th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc [[Edward Overton, Jr.]]\n|-\n| Artillery\n|\n* [[7th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 7th Battery (G)]]: Cpt Adelbert B. Twitchell\n* New York Light, 34th Battery: Cpt Jacob Roemer\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\n[[United States Colored Troops|Fourth Division]]<ref name=not>Not engaged</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Edward Ferrero]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Joshua K. Sigfried\n|\n* [[27th United States Colored Infantry Regiment|27th United States Colored Troops]]: Ltc Charles J. Wright\n* [[30th United States Colored Infantry Regiment|30th United States Colored Troops]]: Col [[Delavan Bates]]\n* [[39th United States Colored Infantry Regiment|39th United States Colored Troops]]: Col Ozora P. Stearns\n* [[43rd United States Colored Infantry Regiment|43rd United States Colored Troops]]: Ltc H. Seymour Hall\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Henry Goddard Thomas|Henry G. Thomas]]\n|\n* [[30th Connecticut Infantry Regiment (Colored)|30th Connecticut Colored]] (detachment): Cpt Charles Robinson\n* [[19th United States Colored Infantry Regiment|19th United States Colored Troops]]: Ltc Joseph G. Perkins\n* [[23rd United States Colore