. Bragg]]\n* [[7th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Wisconsin]]: Col William W. Robinson\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James C. Rice]]\n|\n* [[76th New York Volunteer Infantry|76th New York]]: Ltc John E. Cook '''(w)'''\n* [[14th Brooklyn|84th New York]] (14th Militia): Col [[Edward B. Fowler]]\n* [[95th New York Volunteer Infantry|95th New York]]: Col Edward Pye\n* [[147th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|147th New York]]:  Col Francis C. Miller '''(w&c)'''\n* [[56th Pennsylvania Infantry|56th Pennsylvania]]: Col J. William Hofmann\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Roy Stone]]<ref>Accidentally disabled May 6, 1864</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Edward S. Bragg\n|\n* [[121st Pennsylvania Infantry|121st Pennsylvania]]: Cpt Samuel T. Lloyd\n* [[142nd Pennsylvania Infantry|142nd Pennsylvania]]: Maj Horatio N. Warren\n* [[143rd Pennsylvania Infantry|143rd Pennsylvania]]: Col Edmund L. Dana\n* [[149th Pennsylvania Infantry|149th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc John Irvin\n* [[150th Pennsylvania Infantry|150th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt George W. Jones\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles S. Wainwright]]\n|\n* [[3rd Massachusetts Light Artillery|Massachusetts Light, Battery C]]: Cpt [[Augustus Pearl Martin|Augustus P. Martin]]\n* Massachusetts Light, Battery E: Cpt Charles A. Phillips\n* 1st New York Light, Battery D: Cpt George B. Winslow ('''w''')\n* 1st New York Light, Batteries E and L: Lt George Breck\n* 1st New York Light, Battery H: Cpt Charles E. Mink\n* [[4th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|4th New York Heavy, 2nd Battalion]]: Maj William Arthur\n* [[Battery B, 1st Pennsylvania Light Artillery|1st Pennsylvania Light, Battery B]]: Cpt James H. Cooper\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery B|4th United States, Battery B]]: Lt [[James Stewart (artilleryman)|James Stewart]]\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery D|5th United States, Battery D]]: Lt [[Benjamin F. Rittenhouse]]\n|}\n\n====[[VI Corps (Union Army)|VI Corps]]====\nMG [[John Se