y was wounded May 6, 1864, and was succeeded in command of the First, Second, and Fourth Brigades by Brigadier General Wheaton, who was relieved by Brigadier General Neill early on the morning of May 7, 1864, when the Division was reunited</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[George W. Getty]] '''(w)'''\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Frank Wheaton\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG Thomas H. Neill\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Frank Wheaton]]\n|\n* [[62nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|62nd New York]]: Col David J. Nevin\n* [[93rd Pennsylvania Infantry|93rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc John S. Long, Maj John I. Nevin '''(w)'''\n* [[98th Pennsylvania Infantry|98th Pennsylvania]]: Col John F. Ballier\n* [[102nd Pennsylvania Infantry|102nd Pennsylvania]]: Col John W. Patterson '''(k)'''\n* [[139th Pennsylvania Infantry|139th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc William H. Moody, Maj Abraham H. Snyder '''(k)'''\n|-\n| [[1st Vermont Brigade|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Lewis A. Grant]]\n|\n* [[2nd Vermont Infantry|2nd Vermont]]: Col Newton Stone '''(k)''', Ltc John S. Tyler '''(mw)'''\n* [[3rd Vermont Infantry|3rd Vermont]]: Col [[Thomas O. Seaver]]\n* [[4th Vermont Infantry|4th Vermont]]: Col [[George P. Foster]] '''(w)'''\n* [[5th Vermont Infantry|5th Vermont]]: Ltc John R. Lewis '''(w)'''\n* [[6th Vermont Infantry|6th Vermont]]: Col Elisha L. Barney '''(mw)'''\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas H. Neill]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Daniel D. Bidwell\n|\n* [[7th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|7th Maine]]: Col Edwin C. Mason\n* 43rd New York: Ltc John Wilson '''(k)''', Maj John Fryer '''(k)'''\n* [[49th New York Volunteer Infantry|49th New York]]: Col [[Daniel D. Bidwell]]\n* [[77th New York Volunteer Infantry|77th New York]]: Maj Nathan S. Babcock\n* [[61st Pennsylvania Infantry|61st Pennsylvania]]: Col George F. Smith\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry L. Eustis]]\n|\n* [[7th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|7th Massachusetts]]: Col Thomas D. Johns\n* [[10th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|10th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Joseph B. Parsons\n* [[37th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|37th Massachusetts]]: Col [[Oliver Edwards]]\n* [[2nd Rhode Island Infantry|2nd Rhode Island]]: Ltc Samuel B. M. Read\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nThird Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James B. Ricketts]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William H. Morris]]\n|\n* [[14th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|14th New Jersey]]: Ltc Caldwell K. Hall\n* [[106th New York Volunteer Infantry|106th New York]]: Ltc Charles Townsend\n* [[151st New York Volunteer Infantry|151st New York]]: Ltc Thomas M. Fay\n* [[87th Pennsylvania Infantry|87th Pennsylvania]]: Col John W. Schall\n* [[10th Vermont Infantry|10th Vermont]]: Ltc [[William W. Henry]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Truman Seymour]] '''(c)'''\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Benjamin F. Smith\n|\n* 6th Maryland: Col John W. Horn\n* [[110th Ohio Infantry|110th Ohio]]: Col [[J. Warren Keifer]] '''(w)''', Maj William S. McElwain '''(k)'''\n* [[122nd Ohio Infantry|122nd Ohio]]: Col William H. Ball\n* [[126th Ohio Infantry|126th Ohio]]: Col Benjamin F. Smith\n* 67th Pennsylvania (detachment): Cpt George W. Guss\n* [[138th Pennsylvania Infantry|138th Pennsylvania]]: Col Matthew R. McClennan\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles H. Tompkins]]\n|\n* [[4th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 4th Battery]]: Lt Melville C. Kimball\n* Massachusetts Light, 1st Battery (A): Cpt William H. McCartney\n* New York Light, 1st Battery: Cpt [[Andrew Cowan (artillerist)|Andrew Cowan]]\n* [[3rd New York Independent Light Artillery|New York Light, 3rd Battery]]: Cpt [[William A. Harn]]\n* [[4th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|4th New York Heavy, 1st Battalion]]: Maj Thomas D. Sears\n* [[Battery C, 1st Rhode Island Light Artillery|1st Rhode Island Light, Battery C]]: Cpt Richard Waterman\n* [[Battery E, 1st Rhode Island Light Artillery|1st Rhode Island L