nd United States, Battery M: Lt [[Alexander C. M. Pennington, Jr.]]\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery A|4th United States, Battery A]]: Lt [[Rufus King, Jr.]]\n* 4th United States, Batteries [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery C|C]] and E: Lt Charles L. Fitzhugh\n|}\n\n====Artillery====\nBG [[Henry Jackson Hunt|Henry J. Hunt]]<ref>Chief of Artillery to the whole Army</ref><ref>1st Brigade Horse Artillery detached with Cavalry Corps; 2nd Brigade Horse Artillery attached to the Artillery Reserve (''see: Hunt's report'')</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nArtillery Reserve\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Henry S. Burton\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[J. Howard Kitching]]\n|\n* [[6th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|6th New York Heavy]]: Ltc Edmund R. Travis\n* 15th New York Heavy: Col Louis Schirmer\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj John A. Tompkins\n|\n* [[5th Maine Battery|Maine Light, 5th Battery (E)]]: Cpt [[Greenleaf T. Stevens]]\n* [[Battery A, 1st New Jersey Light Artillery|1st New Jersey Light, Battery A]]: Cpt [[William Hexamer]]\n* [[Battery B, 1st New Jersey Light Artillery|1st New Jersey Light, Battery B]]: Cpt [[A. Judson Clark]]\n* [[5th New York Independent Light Artillery|New York Light, 5th Battery]]: Cpt [[Elijah D. Taft]]\n* New York Light, 12th Battery: Cpt George F. McKnight\n* 1st New York Light, Battery B: Cpt Albert S. Sheldon\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj Robert H. Fitzhugh\n|\n* [[9th Massachusetts Light Artillery|Massachusetts Light, 9th Battery]]: Cpt John Bigelow\n* New York Light, 15th Battery: Cpt Patrick Hart\n* 1st New York Light, Battery C: Lt William H. Phillips\n* New York Light, 11th Battery: Cpt John E. Burton\n* [[Battery H, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery H]]: Lt William A. Ewing\n* 5th United States, Battery E: Lt John R. Brinckle\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade Horse Artillery<ref name=not/>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nC